# SFGGC Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js static website for the San Francisco Golden Gate Classic bowling tournament. The project follows a specific structure and conventions.

## Key Architecture

- **Framework**: Next.js 14 with React 18
- **Styling**: Bootstrap 5 + SCSS modules
- **Theme**: Custom Bootstrap color modes with dark/light/auto support
- **Analytics**: Vercel Analytics
- **Build**: Static site generation

## Directory Structure

- [src/pages/](mdc:src/pages/) - Next.js pages (routing)
- [src/components/](mdc:src/components/) - React components organized by feature
- [src/scss/](mdc:src/scss/) - Global SCSS styles and Bootstrap customization
- [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils/) - Utility functions and context providers
- [src/images/](mdc:src/images/) - Optimized images organized by category
- [public/](mdc:public/) - Static assets and results PDFs

## Component Organization

Each component lives in its own directory with:
- `ComponentName.js` - React component
- `ComponentName.module.scss` - Component-specific styles

## Key Files

- [src/pages/_app.js](mdc:src/pages/_app.js) - App wrapper with Bootstrap and Analytics
- [src/components/layout/layout.js](mdc:src/components/layout/layout.js) - Root layout with theme provider
- [src/utils/ThemeContext.js](mdc:src/utils/ThemeContext.js) - Theme management context
- [src/scss/sfggc.scss](mdc:src/scss/sfggc.scss) - Main stylesheet
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts

## Mobile-First Design

The project uses mobile-first responsive design with Bootstrap breakpoints. Always consider mobile viewports first, then adapt for larger screens.